OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FKeep cake away from office,
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsays food adviser          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, If you work in an office, you know the 
OL,6, drill. It's someone's birthday and the 
OL,7, unwritten rules mean they or a generous
OL,8, boss supplies cake (or cakes) for all. 
OL,10,FBut is it time to kick the cupcakes, to
OL,11,Fget the gateaux away? A food adviser   
OL,12,Fsays workers should not bring in sweet 
OL,13,Ftreats - to avoid tempting colleagues. 
OL,15,FFood Standards Agency chairwoman Prof  
OL,16,FSusan Jebb compared being around cake  
OL,17,Fin the office to passive smoking.      
OL,19,FShe said: "If nobody brought cakes into
OL,20,Fthe office, I would not eat cakes."    
